He taught me to be kind but honest, open minded but critical, polite but firm and compassionate but level-headed.

  - Jordan Boyle (jordanboyle@gmail.com)

As a child, he always made me feel safe ‚Äì even when climbing a mountain or sailing stormy seas. 

Over 38 years, his unconditional love, wise guidance and stellar example have shaped me into a man I am proud to be.

He was a great man and an exceptional journalist, but he was also the most wonderful father anyone could hope to have. Some of my earliest memories are of projects we did together, like the model rocket whose parachute worked so well we never saw it again.

Brendan Boyle, my father, died peacefully at home on Sunday evening. The tragedy of his death cannot be overstated, but my mother, brother and I have been touched to read all the kind words being written about him. It is comforting to know that we are not alone in our sadness.

2. What ways can LGBTQIA+ folk form solidarity & share love with one another, especially during this time? 

#PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDayüåà

"We celebrate Pride today & everyday - LGBTQI+ children have a right to equality & to self-determine their sexual orientation, gender identity, & gender expression!" - Tshegofatso Phala #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

"The education system ought to be one that nurtures, supports, & respects the sexual & gender diversity of LGBTQI+  learners. There is further the need to continue supporting the demand for inclusive education curricula for LGBTQI+ learners." - Tshegofatso Phala #PrideEveryMonth

@EElawcentre, Executive Director: Tshegofatso Phala

"Whilst the laws & policy frameworks in SA are celebrated for progressiveness, LGBTQI+ learners continue to navigate a cis-heteronormative education system where bullying, stigma, & discrimination continue." #PrideEveryMonth https://t.co/0CVq0mBPta

"I pray we as EE become an open & safe space as we see ourselves. I really pray we learn & unlearn. I have breathed within that space. I truly pray we really turn to be as inclusive as we wish & when we do we are ready to take it all.‚Äù - Andiswa Boya #PrideEveryMonth

"I pray we become more open about real stuff that affects the marginalised within the space & always be willing to engage & share our thoughts truthfully in a safe space." - Andiswa Boya #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

"I am still trying to find my feet, my space at EE but also I pray the space becomes more transparent & real as it is on policies & on its membership constitution. I pray it becomes more intellectual & more accepting." - Andiswa Boya #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

"It means apologising for being "too emotional/too womxn", it means being liberated & celebrated as a black person but I'm not really sure what that means for womxn, for me yet." - Andiswa Boya #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

"I AM A BLACK QUEER WOMXN & that is who I am every day & that's who SA cannot accept. To be in a movement like EE means being "all three" at the same time, black queer womxn but having to fight and try to breathe within the space." - Andiswa Boya #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

"I can't be fully out & proud because I have to choose. My freedom comes with either choosing to be queer, womxn, or black in a day. I can't be all three or I'll suffocate to death. Well, I suffocate every day when I have to choose because I can't."- Andiswa Boya #PrideEveryMonth

"You have to constantly apologise for being both as if you are asking for too much acceptance or attention. I am not just any queer womxn in SA, I am a black queer womxn in SA therefore I am automatically at the bottom & seeking attention." - Andiswa Boya #PrideEveryMonth

EE, WC Facilitator: Andiswa Boya 

‚ÄúBeing queer & a womxn has always been separated. You could finally be a womxn but not queer too. Being & seeing both at the same time has always been a fight. If not with self then with the country & community." #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay https://t.co/9xdK9yhinI

"To me being gay inside EE is a blessing in disguise because each & everyone is getting educated. People are supportive &  they know how to treat us in a good way. I really do appreciate the love and support that EE is giving us.‚Äù - Kamohelo Mofoke #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

"Words like this continue to perpetuate violence & hate towards us. People & communities are not educated about our sexuality, hence we need to continue to educate our communities." - Kamohelo Mofoke #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

Equaliser, GP : Kamohelo Mofokeng 

‚ÄúFor me, it‚Äôs a bit hard being openly gay because society treats us badly. They often have hateful words like moffies & stabane. These words demean us and can cause low self-esteem in one‚Äôs life." #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay https://t.co/pKhk0jokFs

"I've grown emotionally, physically, & mentally. It's now about me advocating for human rights in every way I know how. So, let them love what they want to love, accept, understand & live with & I'll stand with being gay every second of my life‚Äù - Nkululeko Ndima #PrideEveryMonth

"I don't want to force my family to accept me. I just want them to UNDERSTAND the life I'm living. Since I've joined EE life has changed because I've been talking to people & I've found a family that loves, understands & accepts me" - Nkululeko Ndima #PrideEveryMonth

"Being victimised by a family member cuts so deep & there's nothing you can do about that when you don't have the support & care you need at that time. When you can't feel the love of your family you go through a lot." - Nkululeko Ndima #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

"It's a traumatic experience that a lot of queer people have to deal with because of the continuous violence against us. I've been hurting for the longest time & I still do because all I want is justice." - Nkululeko Ndima #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay

"My experience since I came out was tough because I got abused twice & it made me hate the world so bad, even the people in it. Being a survivor of abuse is not easy & it's not something that will pass overnight." - Nkululeko Ndima #PrideEveryMonth #PrideEveryDay
